Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sadako Ogata, UN High Commissioner for Refugees, 
arrived in Maputo this afternoon to review progress made in the 
repatriation of about 1.7 million Mozambican refugees. During 
her stay in Mozambique, Sadako Ogata will hold meetings with 
President Joaquim Chissano, senior government and Mozambique 
National Resistance officials, and ambassadors from donor 
countries. She is also expected to visit Tete Province to 
familiarize herself with projects for the reintegration of 
civilians in Angonia District, which harbors more than 200,000 
Mozambican refugees returning from Malawi. 

